  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACC BUSINESS INTEGRITY PROJECT</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project intends to strengthen the integrity of doing business in Ghana by coordinating a quarterly meeting of all key stakeholders in businesses. This coordinated strategy of GII is to help stir the fight against corruption from the compartmentalized approach to controlling corruption to a more comprehensive and inclusive approach where consensus will be built on strategies and workable solutions. It is intended to open space for the policy tripod (Business Policy Makers, Policy Implementors and Business People) to directly discuss challenges and solutions provided or commitments made to provide solution by the various public authorities representing either policy makers and policy implementer s. The specific objectives are:  - to contribute to the promotion of compliance to business regulations by private businesses and ensure service with integrity by the public sector, -  holding government accountable for its new business-related interventions - Paperless Port, National Identification, the issuance of Tax Identification Number by GRA and the issues of tax reliefs; - to help stir the fight against corruption from the compartmentalized approach to a coordinated and facilitated approach which uses consensus building to promote business integrity in Ghana Broadly, the forum will coordinate the deliberation of private sector challenges with corruption and consider current tools, approaches, mechanisms and legal frameworks employed to combat the canker. The forum will further seek to create a community of practice that enables businesses to share with and learn from one another, anti-bribery and anti-corruption policies that promote transparent and accountable business practices and build basic self-monitoring mechanisms that would enhance compliance among forum business sector participants.</narrative>
  </description>
